# mcporter

mcporter is a CLI tool for calling MCP servers to interact with external services.

## Available Servers

Check available servers before use:

```bash
mcporter list 2>&1 | cat
```

The following is for reference only. Trust the output of `mcporter list` for the actual server status.

- `analytics-mcp` — Google Analytics 4: run reports and realtime reports, get account/property summaries, custom dimensions and metrics, Google Ads links, and property annotations
- `aws-mcp` — AWS CLI commands, documentation search, regional availability checks, and SOPs
- `chrome-devtools` — Browser automation via Chrome DevTools Protocol: click, navigate, fill forms, take screenshots/snapshots, evaluate JS, Lighthouse audits, performance traces, network/console inspection, and more
- `drawio` — Open draw.io editor with diagrams from XML, CSV, or Mermaid syntax
- `exa` — AI-powered web search and page content extraction via Exa; supports semantic queries and category filters (company, people)
- `home-assistant` — Home Assistant smart home control: entities, devices, areas, automations, scripts, services, HACS, dashboards, history, statistics, templates, todo lists, zones, backups, and more
- `ticktick` — TickTick task management: projects, tasks (create, update, complete, search, filter, batch), checklists, reminders, recurring tasks, and user preferences
- `unifi-network` — UniFi Network Controller: WiFi networks, clients, devices, switches, APs, firewall, VPN, routing, and statistics, and more
- `zabbix` — Zabbix full API access: hosts, host groups, items, triggers, events, problems, alerts, dashboards, SLA, maintenance windows, templates, discovery rules, actions, scripts, users, proxies, and more
{{- if eq .chezmoi.hostname "7cf34ded5d65" }}
- `amazon-quick-mcp` — Amazon Quick (formerly QuickSight): dashboards, analyses, datasets, data sources, and SQL lineage; Q Topics natural-language queries; Spaces and documents; deep research reports; and the Quick assistant chat
- `amazon-sharepoint-mcp` — SharePoint and OneDrive file operations (list, read, write, search)
- `atoz-mcp` — Amazon AtoZ HR data: compensation (pay, RSU, stock), career (reviews, feedback, goals), benefits (HSA, 401K, elections), tax/payroll, documents, and Aza HR chat
- `aws-gitlab-mcp` — GitLab (gitlab.aws.dev): projects, groups, merge requests, pipelines, CI/CD jobs, repository files, issues, branches, commits, users, bindles, and topics
- `aws-outlook-mcp` — Outlook email (read, search, send, reply, draft, attachments) and calendar (view, create, book rooms, check availability)
- `aws-sentral-mcp` — Salesforce/CRM data: accounts, contacts, opportunities, tasks, events, PFRs, and SIFT activities
- `builder-mcp` — Internal dev tools: code reviews, pipelines, ticketing, oncall, Brazil builds, Apollo deployments, Quip, internal search, SAS risks, internal websites, acronym lookup, Mechanic tools, remote test runs, and workspace/Git info
- `concur-mcp` — SAP Concur expense management: expense reports (create, submit, recall, duplicate), expenses (add, update, delete, itemize), receipt upload and OCR, mileage, attendees, and available expenses from card feeds
- `hs-kmine-mcp` — Proxy for AWS Highspot and KnowledgeMine: natural-language content search and LLM-powered instant answers across the Highspot/KnowledgeMine library, with optional spot ID filtering and personalized results
- `loop-mcp` — Microsoft Loop page reading: fetch and extract content from Loop pages as markdown, supporting both Loop app URLs (loop.cloud.microsoft) and SharePoint-hosted Loop URLs
- `pippin-mcp` — Pippin design document management: projects, artifacts, reviews, comments, reviewer assignments, and local/remote sync
- `slack-mcp` — Slack messages (search, post, react), channels, threads, files, DMs, and reminders
{{- end }}

## Usage

Run `--help` to check the latest usage and available options, then decide how to call the tool.

```bash
mcporter --help 2>&1 | cat
mcporter list <server> --schema 2>&1 | grep -B20 -A20 "<keyword1>" | grep -B20 -A20 "<keyword2>" | cat
mcporter call <server>.<tool> [key=value ...] 2>&1 | cat
```

## Tips

- Always pipe output to `cat` to prevent pager from hanging the AI process
- Run searches across multiple servers in parallel
- When looking up tools with `--schema`, chain multiple `grep` commands to AND-search by keywords (e.g., `grep -B20 -A20 "room" | grep -B20 -A20 "booking"`). A single keyword often matches too many tools and wastes context
- When creating `ticktick` tasks, omit `startDate` and `dueDate` time components unless the user explicitly specifies a time. Use date-only values (e.g., `2026-06-08`) to avoid unnecessary reminders.
- When creating tasks in `ticktick` or `aws-outlook-mcp`, write titles in English using imperative mood (e.g., "Review PR feedback", "Submit expense report").
- `unifi-network` uses a two-step workflow: call `unifi_tool_index` to discover tools, then `unifi_execute` to run them. Use parentheses syntax: `mcporter call 'unifi-network.unifi_execute(tool: "unifi_list_clients")'`
{{- if eq .chezmoi.hostname "7cf34ded5d65" }}
- To read an `amazon-sharepoint-mcp` file from a share URL, do not call `sharepoint_read_file` with the raw URL (it fails with 400). First call `sharepoint_resolve_url url=<share URL>` to get `siteUrl` and `serverRelativeUrl`, then call `sharepoint_read_file siteUrl=<...> serverRelativeUrl=<...> inline=true` to get the content as text. Without `inline=true`, `sharepoint_read_file` requires a `savePath` to download to.
- To read a `loop-mcp` page (`loop_page_read`), passing the `https://loop.cloud.microsoft/p/<base64>` URL directly often fails with "Missing drive_id or item_id in nav params". Instead, decode the IDs locally and pass them as `driveId` / `itemId`: base64-decode the path segment to get `{"u": "<sharepoint url>"}`, then base64-decode that URL's `nav` query param to get `s=...&d=<driveId>&f=<itemId>&...`. The `d=` value is `driveId` and the `f=` value is `itemId`. Then call `loop_page_read driveId=<...> itemId=<...>`.
- To look up a person's alias, role, or team via Phonetool, use `builder-mcp.InternalSearch` with `domain=PHONETOOL`: `mcporter call builder-mcp.InternalSearch query="<person name>" domain=PHONETOOL`. Do not use `ReadInternalWebsites` on the Phonetool search page (it needs AEA auth and fails).
{{- end }}
